createPool(address,address).details: Creates a new Pool contract for the provided token pair and stores the pool address.

params.thatToken: The address of the second token in the pool.
params.thisToken: The address of the first token in the pool.

returns._0: The address of the newly created Pool contract.

getAllPools().details: Returns the list of all pool addresses.

returns._0: An array containing the addresses of all pools.

grantPrivilege(address).details: Can only be called by the owner.

params.account: The address to grant the privileged role.

revokePrivilege(address).details: This function can only be called by the owner.

params.account: The address of the account to have its PRIVILEGED_ROLE revoked.

setDevelopmentFundAddress(address).details: Sets the development fund address to the provided address. Can only be called by the owner of the contract.

params._developmentFundAddress: The new address to be set as the development fund address.

setRoutingAgentShare(uint256).details: Sets the share of the routing agent in the form of a percentage (using full precision, e.g., 10 ** 18 = 100%). Can only be called by the owner of the contract. Routing agent share cannot exceed 100% (expressed as 10 ** 18 for full precision).

params._routingAgentShare: The new routing agent share amount (using full precision).

setUpkeepAllocation(uint256).details: Sets the allocation for the upkeep of the protocol in the form of a percentage (using full precision, e.g., 10 ** 18 = 100%). Can only be called by the owner of the contract. Allocation cannot exceed 100% (expressed as 10 ** 18 for full precision).

params._upkeepAllocation: The new upkeep allocation (using full precision).

grantPrivilege(address).notice: Grants privilege to the specified account.

revokePrivilege(address).notice: Revokes the PRIVILEGED_ROLE from the specified account.
